                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12800753" author="ogrisel" created="Fri, 15 Jan 2010 16:56:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch attached. Note that by default the old behaviour is preserved (chunks are created on the local FS without CRC checksums).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12801421" author="ogrisel" created="Sun, 17 Jan 2010 15:40:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;new version of the patch to provide credentials to both s3:// and s3n:// URL schemes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803603" author="srowen" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2010 04:53:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ready to commit this too: is there an extra slash in the path you now construct? looks like there is a &quot;//chunk&quot; in there. Also does this still work with local files, does a &quot;file://&quot; URL work?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803675" author="ogrisel" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2010 11:38:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Right for the extra /. It&apos;s harmless but ugly in the source code, please remove it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As for the second question, I confirm that local files still work as previously (without url scheme) or using explicitly the &lt;a href=&quot;file:///&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;file:///&lt;/a&gt; scheme. I will attach a new patch to make this more explicit in the commandline options help.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12803676" author="ogrisel" created="Fri, 22 Jan 2010 11:39:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;New version of the patch with better command line options help&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
